---
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import GrainDivider from '../components/GrainDivider.astro';
import MusicCard from '../components/MusicCard.astro';

const entries = (await getCollection('music')).sort(
  (a, b) => b.data.date.valueOf() - a.data.date.valueOf()
);
---

<BaseLayout title="Music" description="Guitar covers, tone experiments, and covers.">
  <section class="wrap">
    <div class="eyebrow">Music</div>
    <h1>Guitar, tone, and collaboration</h1>
    <p class="prose">
      I play acoustic and electric guitar: mostly recording covers, chasing tone, and jamming!
      with my friends. Tasteful playing over shredding, always. My biggest musical influence is Tommy Emmanuel, CGP, whose musicianship and ability to make a single guitar sound like an entire band continues to inspire me.
I'm also a lifelong admirer of The Beatles, especially George Harrison for his tasteful songwriting and understated guitar work.
Blues has been another major influence on my playing, with legends like Stevie Ray Vaughan, Jimi Hendrix, Eric Clapton, and B.B. King shaping how I think about phrasing, feel, and tone.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="wrap">
    <div class="grid grid-2">
      <div class="reveal">
        <h2>Musical Influences</h2>
        <p class="muted">
  Beyond playing the guitar, I'm simply someone who loves listening to music. I enjoy exploring different genres, traditions, and cultures, and the more I listen, the more I realize how much there is to learn. Jazz fascinates me for its harmony, improvisation, while Indian classical music has taught me to appreciate melody, rhythm, and the emotional depth of a performance.
  Much of that appreciation began at home. My mother has always loved Hindustani classical music and has been learning and singing it for many years. Growing up, I often heard her practicing at home or softly humming while going about her day. Through her, I was introduced to the timeless voices of Lata Mangeshkar, Asha Bhosle, Mohammed Rafi, and Kishore Kumar, along with countless beautiful compositions that continue to stay with me. Those early experiences quietly shaped the way I listen to music today.
  My playlists jump between all sorts of different genres. Alongside blues and rock, I enjoy Marathi songs, Natya-Sangeet and Abhangas, Bengali music, Uttarakhandi folk songs, Bollywood music across generations, Western classical music, orchestral scores (especially those by Hans Zimmer) and, of course, Indian classical music. I don't really have a favourite genre; I simply enjoy discovering music that is honest, expressive, and which comes from within the artist, regardless of its language, style, or era.
</p>
      </div>
      <div class="reveal">
        <h2>Equipment</h2>
        <div class="stack">
          <p><strong>Guitars:</strong> <span class="muted">Newen TSA-013 TL, Yamaha F310</span></p>
          <p><strong>Amplifiers:</strong> <span class="muted">Carlsbro Sherwood 20R, Fender Frontman 10G (lil but cute)</span></p>
          <p><strong>Recording setup:</strong> <span class="muted">[Behringer UPHORIA UMC22, John Mayer Archetype Plini, Amplitube 5]</span></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="wrap"><GrainDivider /></div>

  <section class="wrap">
    <h2>Videos, performances &amp; collaborations</h2>
    <p class="prose">
      Add a new Markdown file to <span class="mono">src/content/music/</span> with a
      <span class="mono">youtubeId</span> and it appears here automatically — no page edits required.
    </p>
    <div class="grid grid-auto">
      {entries.map((e) => (
        <div class="reveal">
          <MusicCard
            title={e.data.title}
            type={e.data.type}
            date={e.data.date}
            youtubeId={e.data.youtubeId}
            platform={e.data.platform}
            duration={e.data.duration}
            description={e.data.description}
          />
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="wrap">
    <h2>Upcoming performances</h2>
    <p class="muted">[I have no idea honestly]</p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
